column1: # Test Scenario: Check agent registration failure when environment is not correct

column2: Press “Win + E” keys, open File Explorer, go to the folder where “cmdextension.msi” locates
Press “Win + E” keys, open File Explorer, go to the folder where “cmdextension.msi” locates
Wait 3 minutes, and go to validation

Open file explorer, go to %ProgramData%\Microsoft\CMDExtension\Logs. 
Open “CMDExtension.log”
column3:
1. Verify there are failure logs and retry attempts.

·     “InvalidHttpResponse. StatusCode: 401”
2. There is no plugin logs (Such as HeartbeatPlugin.log)

column2:
Press “Win + R” keys, type “wbemtest” and press Enter. 
Click on “Connect”, type “root\cmd\clientagent” and press Enter. 
Click on “Enum Instances”, type “SchedulerEntity” and press Enter.
column3: Verify the list of instances is empty.

column2:
Test Cleanup:


In the same powershell window as “Step 3”, run command: msiexec /x cmdextension.msi
